Casting Fool <jester(-at-)cfnson.com> wrote:
> I ordered a bushing, but am wondering if it's just plastic.  If so, is it
> going to fit the wallowed out hole well enough to stay put?

Yes, cheap translucent clear plastic.
The bushing should not be loose in the hole.
Repair the original hole with a plate of thin sheet metal.
Drill the correct size hole and mig or rivet the plate,
centered over the original. The additional thickness should
not interfere with the new bushing.
Dave
